Type: Null is a Normal type Pokémon introduced in Generation 7.

The shapes of its front and hind legs are different, as Type: Null was constructed to synthesize the strengths of various Pokémon, enabling it to adapt to any situation.

The mask fitted to Type: Null's head is a piece of equipment designed to control its latent powers. It's extremely heavy, so it also serves to hinder Type: Null's agility.
